Package eu.advance.logistics.flow.engine.error

Compilation error classes.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
HasBinding Interface to represent an error having the reference to a specific binding.
HasTypes Interface to indicate the error contains type information.
 

Class Summary
CombinedTypeError The combination (e.g., union) of two types could not be created.
ConcreteVsParametricTypeError The wire binds a concrete type and a parametric type which cannot be in subtype relation.
ConstantBlockTypeSyntaxError The constant block type field contains invalid type syntax.
ConstantOutputError A wire is bound to a constant on its destination side.
DestinationToCompositeInputError The wire's destination is bound to an input port of the parent composite block's.
DestinationToCompositeOutputError The wire's destination is bound to an output port of a composite block (not the parent block).
DestinationToOutputError The wire's destination is bound to an output port of a block.
ErrorLookup Utility class to store and manage creator functions for various compilation error classes.
GeneralCompilationError A general compilation error indicator when the error details are stored in XML.
IncompatibleBaseTypesError The wire binds two parametric types which have incompatible base types or number of arguments.
IncompatibleTypesError The wire binds two concrete types where the left type does not extend or equals to the right type.
MissingBlockError The referenced block type cannot be found.
MissingDestinationError The destination object of the binding cannot be found.
MissingDestinationPortError The destination port of the destination object cannot be found.
MissingSourceError The source object of the binding cannot be found.
MissingSourcePortError The source port of the source object cannot be found.
MissingVarargsError The referenced varargs parameter is missing.
MultiInputBindingError An input port is bound to multiple outputs at the same time.
NonVarargsError The referenced parameter is not a varargs parameter.
SourceToCompositeInputError The source (input) of the binding points to a composite input port in the same level (and not the parent composite's input).
SourceToCompositeOutputError The source of the binding points to the output port of the enclosing composite's output port.
SourceToInputBindingError The wire's source is bound to an input port of an block.
TypeArgumentCountError The wire binds two parametric types with different type argument count.
UnsetVarargsError The varargs parameter has no counts set in the block reference.
